    "faq": {
      "type": "lsc-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is Structural Lift Therapy?",
            "answer": "<p>Structural Lift Therapy is a non-surgical face lift treatment powered by EM LIFT technology. It uses targeted electromagnetic energy to stimulate deep facial muscle contractions, strengthening and toning the muscles that support facial structure.</p><p>Unlike treatments that add volume, this approach enhances your natural facial support from within.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How is this different from fillers or other injectables?",
            "answer": "<p>Structural Lift Therapy does not add volume or freeze muscles.</p><p>• Fillers add volume</p><p>• Anti-wrinkle injections relax muscles</p><p>• Structural Lift Therapy strengthens muscles</p><p>It improves contour and lift naturally by working on the underlying facial structure rather than altering facial expression or shape.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is EM LIFT Safe?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. EM LIFT technology is non-invasive and does not involve needles, injections, or surgery.</p><p>The treatment is delivered in a controlled clinical environment and tailored to your facial anatomy during consultation.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Does the treatment hurt?",
            "answer": "<p>Most patients describe the sensation as strong but comfortable muscle contractions.</p><p>You will feel the muscles working, similar to an intense facial workout, but it should not be painful. Intensity can be adjusted to suit your comfort level.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is there any downtime?",
            "answer": "<p>No.</p><p>You can return to normal activities immediately after treatment. There is typically no redness, swelling, bruising, or peeling.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How many sessions do I need?",
            "answer": "<p>For visible lifting and contour improvement, a course of 4–6 sessions is typically recommended.</p><p>Some patients choose maintenance sessions after completing their initial course to sustain results.</p><p>Your practitioner will recommend a personalised plan during consultation.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_7": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "When will I see results?",
            "answer": "<p>You may feel muscle activation immediately.</p><p>Visible lifting and contour improvement usually develops progressively over 4–12 weeks as muscle tone improves.</p><p>Results build gradually rather than appearing suddenly.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_8": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long do results last?",
            "answer": "<p>Results can last several months after a full treatment course.</p><p>Maintenance sessions are often recommended every few months to support long-term muscle tone and facial structure.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_9": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Who is a non surgical face lift best for?",
            "answer": "<p>It is ideal for patients who:</p><p>• Notice mild to moderate facial laxity</p><p>• Want jawline or cheek definition</p><p>• Prefer a non-surgical face lift</p><p>• Do not want injectables</p><p>• Want natural-looking improvement</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_10": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Will it make my face look unnatural?",
            "answer": "<p>No.</p><p>Structural Lift Therapy works by strengthening your own facial muscles. It does not change facial volume or freeze expression, so results appear natural and progressive.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_11": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is this a replacement for a surgical facelift?",
            "answer": "<p>No.</p><p>Structural Lift Therapy is a non-surgical face lift option designed for patients who want improvement without surgery. It will not replicate the results of a surgical facelift but can significantly improve contour and support for the right candidate.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_12": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How should I prepare for treatment?",
            "answer": "<p>No special preparation is required. You should attend with clean skin and follow any practitioner advice given during consultation.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_13": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What payment options do you offer?",
            "answer": "<p>We offer flexible payment options to make your treatment as convenient as possible. You can choose to pay per single session or pay in full for a course of treatments for better overall value. We accept card, cash, and bank transfer in clinic.</p><p>For added flexibility, we also offer 0% finance through Klarna, allowing you to spread the cost into manageable instalments with a range of payment options available, subject to eligibility.</p><p>If you’re unsure which option is best for you, our team will be happy to guide you.<br/></p><p>If you’re unsure which option is best for you, our team will be happy to guide you during your consultation.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_14": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Does EM Lift hurt?",
            "answer": "<p>No – Emlift is a comfortable, non-invasive treatment.<br/><br/>You’ll feel rhythmic muscle contractions along with gentle warmth as the RF energy penetrates the skin. Most clients find it relaxing and even describe it as a “workout for the face.”</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_15": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do I need to book a consultation before my first session?",
            "answer": "<p>No you don't your consultation is done on the day of your treatment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_16": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is your cancellation policy?",
            "answer": "<p>Cancellations up to 24 hours before your appointment will receive a full refund or can be rescheduled.<br/><br/>Any cancellations on the day can be rescheduled but will not be refunded.<br/><br/>If you do not show to your appointment you will not receive a refund or a reschedule. Please note that we offer email and text appointment reminders right up until 24 hours before your appointment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_17": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What happens if I want to book a course?",
            "answer": "<p>If you want to book a course you can do this at the clinic after your first session. Any discount for booking a course will also he applied.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_18": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "I would like to speak to someone before I book my treatment, how is best to do this?",
            "answer": "<p>If you would like to speak to someone please do one of the below.<br/><br/>- Use the enquiry button.<br/><br/>- Contact us via email at info@laserskinclinics.co.uk<br/><br/>- Call us during opening hours on 01902 256667<br/><br/>- Send us a WhatsApp by clicking the WhatsApp button on the website.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_19": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How many sessions will I need?",
            "answer": "<p>A typical Emlift course includes 4 to 6 sessions, spaced about a week apart.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_20": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Who is EM Lift suitable for?",
            "answer": "<p>Emlift is suitable for anyone who wants to improve facial firmness, definition, and contour without surgery.<br/><br/>It’s ideal for people noticing mild to moderate skin laxity, early signs of ageing, or a loss of facial tone around the cheeks, jawline, and lower face.<br/><br/>Emlift is also a great option for those who prefer natural-looking results and want to stimulate collagen and muscle strength without injectables or downtime.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_21": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How soon will I see results?",
            "answer": "<p>You may notice a subtle lift and tightening immediately after your first treatment, with results continuing to improve over the following weeks as collagen rebuilds and the muscles strengthen.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
